original_title: Visit of Their Majesties the King and Queen to the North-East Coast Shipbuilding and Engineering Works on the Wear
overview: George V and Queen Mary pay a morale boosting visit to the dry docks in the north-east of England in June 1917. Included on the BFI DVD "A Royal Occasion", and also part of the BFI collection "Tales From the Shipyard".
title: Visit of Their Majesties the King and Queen to the North-East Coast Shipbuilding and Engineering Works on the Wear
